# ============================================================
# ENVIRONMENT SETUP GUIDE
# ============================================================
#
# ✅ LOCAL DEVELOPMENT (works out of the box):
#   Frontend: npm run dev       → reads .env.development
#   Backend:  npm run dev       → runs on localhost:5000
#   No manual env setup needed.
#
# ✅ PRODUCTION (Vercel):
#   1. Deploy frontend to Vercel
#   2. In Vercel Dashboard → Project Settings → Environment Variables:
#      Key:   VITE_API_URL
#      Value: https://<your-tunnel>.trycloudflare.com/api
#   3. Redeploy.
#
# ✅ CUSTOM LOCAL SETUP:
#   Copy this file to .env.local and set your own VITE_API_URL.
#   .env.local is gitignored and overrides all other .env files.
#
# ============================================================
# Example — uncomment the line for your scenario:
# ============================================================
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-tunnel.trycloudflare.com/api
